page.title: 17ECOLOGY 3
page.content: CONCLUSION We walked up the south west facing slope which,as you might expect,received a greater amount of sunlight than Sharpitor's north east facing slope.This is proven by the abundance of plant life on the south west slope whereas there is a lack of vegetation on the shady north east slope. All over the open moorland, wild ponies are found. They are generally not moorland ponies but have been interbred with lowland animals. Many local people feel the animals are cruelly neglected by the commoners who own them. A.FORD,N.MAJOR,J.SKINNER, M.RAYMENT,C.STONE, (LOWER SIXTH)
